  "riddle": "1. Seek the page chronicling the accomplishments of a Romanian tennis player whose career peaked in the 1990s; from this, discover how many titles she claimed in singles play.\n\n2. What is the next prime number following your answer from clue 1? \n\n3. In what year did a significant tournament on the hard courts of Flushing Meadows commence, marking a pivotal point in the summer of 1997?\n\n4. This French city hosted a clay court event where tennis stars competed—what city and country might it be?\n\n5. Through the lens of topography, what is the elevation of this charming city known for its picturesque canals and timber-framed houses?\n\n6. As you explore the surroundings, how many churches can be found near this French locale?\n\n7. To proceed, take the elevation you found in clue 5 and add it to the number of churches counted in clue 6.\n\n8. What is the driving distance in kilometers between the captivating clay tournament in clue 4 and the destination of the 1999 event in Egypt?\n\n9. Find the page that tells of a notable clay tournament held in the Italian city celebrated for its stunning coastal views; what are those city and country?\n\n10. Within the history of the tournament you just uncovered, what was the size of the singles draw?\n\n11. Calculate how many days span from the start of the tournament in clue 3 to the not-so-distant future date in March 2026.\n\n12. From your findings in clue 11, what is the largest prime factor of that duration in days?\n\n13. If one were to convert 56 meters into feet, what figure would emerge from this transformation?\n\n14. Combine the total you achieved in clue 7 with the total days from clue 11, then compute the result of that sum modulo 10. The answer will be a single digit (0-9).",
